byline.contributor: James Kanter contributed reporting from Brussels.

abstract: Chaos as migrants land at Piraeus, main port in Greece, points to disconnect between migrant relocation policies set in Brussels and realities on ground in crisis; disarray highlights Europe's ongoing shortcomings in acting on its plans to deal with migrant influx.
lead_paragraph: The situation on the ground is often very different from what is discussed in the conference rooms of Brussels as the tide of desperate people keeps flowing into Europe.

headline.main: As Europe Wrangles Over Migrant Relocation, Reality Moves Faster
headline.print_headline: Disarray and Improvised Rules on Front Lines of Migrant Crisis
